F. Plotting multiple Matplotlib and Seaborn charts in a grid¶

In [7]:
sepal = data['sepal_length']
petal = data['petal_length']
In [12]:
fig, axs = plt.subplots(1,4, figsize=(12,6))
axs[0].scatter(sepal, petal)
axs[0].set_xlabel('sepal_length')
axs[0].set_ylabel('petal_length')
axs[0].set_title('sepal vs petal')

axs[1].plot(sepal, petal, '.', color='blue')
axs[1].set_xlabel('sepal_length')
axs[1].set_ylabel('petal_length')
axs[1].set_title('sepal vs petal')

axs[2].scatter(sepal, petal)
axs[2].set_xlabel('sepal_length')
axs[2].set_ylabel('petal_length')
axs[2].set_title('sepal vs petal')

axs[3].hist(petal)
axs[3].set_xlabel('sepal_length')
axs[3].set_ylabel('#')
axs[3].set_title('sepal vs petal')

plt.tight_layout()
